        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(llm): preserve structured tool results as text",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes an issue where agent sessions could receive literal `(see attached image)` placeholders instead of normal text/JSON tool results when a tool result block was structured but not typed as `text`.\n\nThis replacement PR covers the provider conversion paths from #96895 and also covers the active OpenAI Responses transport path noted in the review there.\n\nCloses #96857\nRelated: #96895\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nTool-result replay code in multiple provider/transport paths only collected blocks with `type: \"text\"`. Structured non-image blocks could therefore be treated as empty output and collapse to an image/no-output fallback. This change adds a bounded shared extractor for structured non-image tool-result blocks and uses it in OpenAI Responses, OpenAI-compatible chat completions, Google/Gemini conversion, and the OpenAI Responses transport converter.\n\nThe current `main` fallback behavior is preserved:\n\n- empty non-image output remains `(no output)` where that fallback already exists;\n- image-only output remains `(see attached image)`;\n- structured non-image output is serialized as text instead of being dropped.\n\n## User Impact\n\nAgents should be able to inspect structured text-like tool output in their model context instead of losing it to an attachment placeholder. This directly improves debugging and agent follow-up reliability when tools return JSON/status-like blocks.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Live issue evidence: #96857 includes current redacted observations where ordinary text/status tool outputs reached an agent-visible context as literal `(see attached image)` placeholders instead of text.\n- Code-path evidence: current `main` filtered tool-result content down to `type: \"text\"` in the affected provider/transport paths; this patch routes those paths through one bounded structured-text extractor.\n- Local pre-check only:\n  - `git diff --check HEAD~1..HEAD` completed without whitespace errors.\n  - The repository pre-commit formatter hook ran `oxfmt --write` on the 10 changed files before commit.\n- GitHub Actions validation: pending on this PR. The PR is draft until the relevant CI/check lanes and real behavior proof are available for the current head SHA.\n\n## Risk\n\n- Message-delivery behavior changes are intentionally limited to structured non-image tool-result blocks that were previously dropped by text-only filtering.\n- Image blocks remain excluded from text extraction, so image-bearing tool outputs keep using the existing image handling path.\n- Structured blocks are serialized with bounded length and circular-reference handling to avoid unbounded replay text.\n\n## Rollback\n\nRevert this PR to restore the previous per-provider text-only extraction behavior. No migration, dependency, workflow, or persistent data changes are included.\n\n## Not Tested / Limitations\n\n- Full CI, typecheck, focused Vitest, and real behavior proof are not complete yet for this replacement PR head.\n- This PR is intentionally draft until those GitHub Actions results are available and the body can be updated with current-head run links/results.\n",
